  <prompt>
    Build `SpeAttachmentSource.tsx` at `subcomponents/sources/SpeAttachmentSource.tsx`. Opens a Fluent `<Dialog>` showing a browseable SPE container picker — user navigates the container hierarchy and selects driveItems to attach.

    On selection, produces `IAttachment[]` with `source='spe'`, `driveItemId: <selected driveItemId>` (canonical per FR-21), `name`, `sizeBytes`, `mimeType` from the SPE driveItem metadata. No local file content — server resolves the driveItem at send time.

    The SPE browser primitive likely already exists in the shared lib (`SpeDocumentViewer` / `SpeContainerBrowser` style component). Audit + reuse — do NOT build a new SPE browser. If no reusable primitive exists, fall back to a minimal `<input>` accepting a driveItemId GUID with a deferred TODO for Wave 6.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend developer with SPE integration awareness; familiar with the shared lib's existing SPE browser primitives.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `SpeAttachmentSource.tsx` compiles + lint-clean. Clicking Add opens an SPE browser; selecting one or more driveItems adds them to AttachmentList with `driveItemId` populated.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-07, SPE is one of 4 sources. SPE containers hold the documents associated with sprk_documents/sprk_matters etc. User picks from a container's contents.

      `driveItemId` is the canonical attachment reference (FR-21 / Wave 0). Server (`CommunicationService.cs`) resolves driveItemId to the actual content via the existing SPE facade (ADR-007) at send time. Client never reaches SPE directly.

      Look for existing browser primitives in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SpeDocumentViewer/`, `SpeContainerBrowser/`, or similar. Reuse what's there.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/subcomponents/sources/SpeAttachmentSource.tsx (NEW)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/subcomponents/AttachmentList.tsx (UPDATE — wire SPE picker)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/index.ts (UPDATE)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/ (READ — find existing SPE browser primitive)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-007">SPE access via existing facade only — client never directly hits SharePoint Embedded APIs</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 only — `Dialog`, `Button`, `Tree` / `List`</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">No direct `@spaarke/auth` import — use injected `authenticatedFetch`</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">Single canonical SPE picker for email attachments — replaces ad-hoc impls</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Selected items produce `IAttachment` with `source: 'spe'` and `driveItemId` populated</constraint>
  </constraints>

