  <steps>
    <step order="1">Grep `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/` for existing SPE browser primitive (e.g., `SpeContainerBrowser`, `SpeDocumentViewer`). Document what's found in task notes.</step>
    <step order="2">If a reusable primitive exists, author `SpeAttachmentSource.tsx`:
      - Props: `{ onAdd: (attachments: IAttachment[]) =&gt; void; containerId?: string; authenticatedFetch: typeof fetch; disabled?: boolean }`
      - Renders a Button "Add from SPE" that opens a Dialog with the existing browser primitive inside
      - On selection, maps driveItems → `IAttachment[]` and calls `onAdd`</step>
    <step order="3">If no reusable primitive exists, ship a minimal driveItem-ID-input picker as a v1 with a CLEAR TODO to replace with a real browser. Note the gap in PR description.</step>
    <step order="4">Wire into AttachmentList — when `attachmentSources` includes `{ kind: 'spe', config: { containerId } }`, render this picker.</step>
    <step order="5">Update `EmailComposer/index.ts` — export `SpeAttachmentSource`.</step>
    <step order="6">Smoke test: open picker, select a known driveItem, verify it appears in AttachmentList with source badge "SPE" + driveItemId set.</step>
    <step order="7">Run `npm run build` + `npm run lint` clean.</step>
    <step order="8">Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 016 ✅.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol.</step>
  </steps>

